The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 599) This re-union concert saw over 500,000 

 Simon amp; Garfunkel fans huddling together in New York?s 

 Central Park on September 19, 1981. The DVD contains the 

 entire show, recorded live. The playlist includes classics 

 like Mrs Robinson, Homeward Bound and America, 

 and lesser-known gems like Slip Sliding Away.

 THE DISPLAY

 (Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 7.30 pm, 

 till October 2) An impressive collection of drawings, etchings 

 and lithographs of Italian artists. Check out the works 

 of Giorgio De Chirico, Renato Guttuso, Corrado Cagli and 

 Giuseppe Capogrossi.

 THE SHOW

 (Crossword 

 Bookstore, 6.45 pm, September 29) A seven-woman cast ? Alokananda 

 Roy, Anindita Sarbadhicary, Deboleena Dutta, June, Renu Roy, 

 Poonam Singh and Sudeshna Roy ? will read and enact excerpts 

 from Eve Ensler?s (in picture below) controversial play The 

 Vagina Monologues. 




